And why give two conflicting orders
for the Pyo op?

362
00:30:29,041 --> 00:30:32,082
You told me to retrieve him,
why give the agents other orders?

363
00:30:32,207 --> 00:30:33,957
You son of a bitch!

364
00:30:36,082 --> 00:30:39,165
We lost 2 agents and Director Pyo,

365
00:30:39,374 --> 00:30:43,874
and Agent Yang is gravely wounded, in a coma.

366
00:30:45,041 --> 00:30:47,999
The 417 and asylum ops,

367
00:30:48,124 --> 00:30:50,290
you fucked them all up.

368
00:30:50,374 --> 00:30:52,707
Are you out of your goddamn mind?!

369
00:30:53,916 --> 00:30:57,291
This is the list of all the bribes you've taken.

370
00:30:57,624 --> 00:30:59,999
Agents risk their lives in the field,

371
00:31:00,082 --> 00:31:03,415
but the KCIA Director fattens himself on bribes.

372
00:31:06,041 --> 00:31:10,541
We kept this agency alive until you came along.

373
00:31:12,874 --> 00:31:15,915
How would the president react to this?

374
00:31:17,082 --> 00:31:20,290
Take the bullet and retire with your honor.

375
00:31:20,374 --> 00:31:24,832
Won't it be wiser to keep
the money you stole thus far?

376
00:31:25,249 --> 00:31:26,874
Park Pyong-ho!

377
00:31:27,457 --> 00:31:29,165
How dare you investigate me?

378
00:31:30,957 --> 00:31:34,373
This is a recording of you and those businessmen.

379
00:31:35,791 --> 00:31:38,457
You've got a week to clear out.

380
00:31:59,249 --> 00:32:01,790
Who said anything about revolution?
We're after reform!

381
00:32:01,874 --> 00:32:03,624
We can't be cornered as left wingers!

382
00:32:03,707 --> 00:32:05,207
The public won't listen to us!

383
00:32:05,291 --> 00:32:07,916
When on earth can you achieve that?

384
00:32:07,999 --> 00:32:10,249
After we're all dead?

385
00:32:10,374 --> 00:32:12,624
Yoo-jung, you tell us, is he right or am I?

386
00:32:12,707 --> 00:32:14,123
Speak up. Who's right?

387
00:32:14,207 --> 00:32:16,873
Let's just go. Yoo-jung, come on.

388
00:32:16,957 --> 00:32:18,915
You son of a bitch! Where you going?!

389
00:32:18,999 --> 00:32:21,874
We came here to find a solution,
why are you leaving?!

390
00:32:21,957 --> 00:32:23,207
Bring him over here!

391
00:32:23,291 --> 00:32:25,791
Back off... Damn you...

392
00:32:27,832 --> 00:32:30,415
Bastard, how could you throw that at a friend?

393
00:32:32,416 --> 00:32:34,374
Stop it! Just stop it!

394
00:32:43,457 --> 00:32:45,540
Thank you, sir.

395
00:32:54,707 --> 00:32:55,998
Where are you going?

396
00:32:58,582 --> 00:33:00,415
I need another drink.

397
00:33:22,499 --> 00:33:24,082
That's enough.

398
00:33:26,374 --> 00:33:29,999
They say a dictator's pawns are
worse than the dictator.

399
00:33:33,874 --> 00:33:36,290
A dictator's pawn...

400
00:33:41,874 --> 00:33:46,374
I don't care what you do,
but don't hang around bad guys.

401
00:33:47,624 --> 00:33:50,457
Don't make me regret bringing you here.

402
00:33:51,791 --> 00:33:53,499
Bad guys?

403
00:33:55,249 --> 00:33:57,582
Who's worse?

404
00:33:59,791 --> 00:34:02,499
How long have you worked for the agency?

405
00:34:10,124 --> 00:34:11,957
13 years.

406
00:34:15,666 --> 00:34:17,874
The world is changing,

407
00:34:19,957 --> 00:34:22,165
but it's still so stupid...

408
00:34:30,707 --> 00:34:32,498
3 years ago, Tokyo

409
00:34:32,582 --> 00:34:34,832
What took you so long?

410
00:34:35,041 --> 00:34:37,791
A pun quiz for you.

411
00:34:38,082 --> 00:34:40,582
Wars that take place in space?

412
00:34:41,999 --> 00:34:43,540
"Star Wars".

413
00:34:43,666 --> 00:34:46,416
A war that takes place in the winter?

414
00:34:46,999 --> 00:34:48,457
"Cold War".

415
00:34:48,541 --> 00:34:53,041
What's a war that never ends?

416
00:34:55,916 --> 00:34:58,124
"Korean War".

417
00:35:01,082 --> 00:35:02,832
That's funny?

418
00:35:03,041 --> 00:35:05,707
Laugh for once, it's called a joke.

419
00:35:05,832 --> 00:35:07,248
Practice,

420
00:35:07,332 --> 00:35:09,957
you're way too serious.

421
00:35:12,082 --> 00:35:15,165
I've been wanting to get
away from everything lately.

422
00:35:15,541 --> 00:35:17,582
That's a great idea.

423
00:35:21,082 --> 00:35:22,915
Where to though?

424
00:35:32,791 --> 00:35:34,707
He's here, we're on!

425
00:35:35,207 --> 00:35:38,165
I always wondered where that beast disappeared to,

426
00:35:38,249 --> 00:35:39,540
but in the end, it's all about love.

427
00:35:39,624 --> 00:35:42,165
Gotta hand it to your intuition.

428
00:35:45,332 --> 00:35:46,998
Stay right behind me!

429
00:35:58,666 --> 00:36:00,291
Won-sik!

430
00:36:01,249 --> 00:36:02,832
Pyong-ho...

431
00:36:03,957 --> 00:36:05,665
I'm sorry...

432
00:36:06,041 --> 00:36:08,999
Soon, somebody will replace me.

433
00:36:26,957 --> 00:36:28,457
Is that Dad?

434
00:36:32,249 --> 00:36:33,749
How old are you?

435
00:36:52,041 --> 00:36:53,457
Yes?

436
00:36:53,457 --> 00:36:55,790
- Sir, it's Ju-kyung.
- Yeah.

437
00:36:55,916 --> 00:36:59,666
The newly appointed director
is head of president's secretary.

438
00:37:01,291 --> 00:37:05,791
Mr. President said,
if the KCIA does not reform, it need not exist.

439
00:37:06,541 --> 00:37:11,041
Our priority must be capturing
North Korean spies who provoke us.

440
00:37:13,249 --> 00:37:16,749
$10,000 reward and
special promotion will be given

441
00:37:16,832 --> 00:37:20,290
to any agent with outstanding performance.

442
00:37:28,499 --> 00:37:32,457
Don't kill me! I'll do what you ask!

443
00:37:33,374 --> 00:37:34,749
Stay right there.

444
00:37:38,249 --> 00:37:39,582
That's enough.

445
00:37:39,666 --> 00:37:41,999
Let's call it a day.

446
00:37:42,416 --> 00:37:46,041
What's the matter? We're almost there.

447
00:37:47,916 --> 00:37:49,332
I said that's enough!

448
00:37:51,124 --> 00:37:52,624
Let's go home.

449
00:37:54,874 --> 00:37:56,957
Let the kids sleep.

450
00:38:06,249 --> 00:38:10,165
A long day?

451
00:38:11,499 --> 00:38:13,124
Get some sleep...

452
00:38:15,749 --> 00:38:19,749
I'm assigned to KCIA starting next week.

453
00:38:20,957 --> 00:38:24,873
I'll report through CEO Choi
at Jupiter Corporation.

454
00:38:24,957 --> 00:38:27,290
- Salute!
- Yes, Sir.

455
00:38:27,332 --> 00:38:28,040
3 years ago, Gwang ju

456
00:38:28,082 --> 00:38:30,123
The commander is approaching!

457
00:38:33,249 --> 00:38:35,374
We got the green light to open fire!

458
00:38:35,457 --> 00:38:36,832
Wipe them all out!

459
00:38:53,624 --> 00:38:55,999
Major Kim, it's been a while!

460
00:38:56,124 --> 00:38:58,040
Congratulations on your promotion.

461
00:38:58,374 --> 00:39:01,999
Pretty cushy working as a public servant?

462
00:39:02,499 --> 00:39:04,874
How long has it been?

463
00:39:05,166 --> 00:39:07,416
4 months now, sir. It's worse than hell.

464
00:39:07,541 --> 00:39:08,999
Sit!

465
00:39:09,457 --> 00:39:13,165
Do you know why the president sent me?

466
00:39:15,916 --> 00:39:18,291
KCIA has gotten too soft!

467
00:39:18,374 --> 00:39:21,874
Government agencies and
press must embrace his governing ethos

468
00:39:21,957 --> 00:39:25,207
for him to relax, is that so hard?

469
00:39:25,624 --> 00:39:27,124
It will be done, sir.

470
00:39:27,499 --> 00:39:29,624
Let's go one step at a time.

471
00:39:30,416 --> 00:39:34,166
I looked over the reports.
We got a mole situation?

472
00:39:34,707 --> 00:39:35,832
Donglim?

473
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:39,123
It's not verified, sir.

474
00:39:39,374 --> 00:39:43,415
If major ops are failing,
there's an underlying problem.

475
00:39:44,499 --> 00:39:46,040
Am I right?

476
00:39:48,374 --> 00:39:50,707
What is this?

477
00:39:51,082 --> 00:39:54,123
Dates when Donglim contacted someone in Japan.

478
00:39:54,582 --> 00:39:59,082
Yang relayed that intel to
my predecessor after the incident.

479
00:40:00,874 --> 00:40:04,249
Cross reference it with everyone in the Pyo op.

480
00:40:04,416 --> 00:40:06,041
The Foreign Unit?

481
00:40:06,166 --> 00:40:08,749
It's not my team, how could I...?

482
00:40:09,791 --> 00:40:12,707
That's why I want you to do it.

483
00:40:14,249 --> 00:40:17,790
Where there's smoke, there's fire.

484
00:40:17,916 --> 00:40:22,416
Strip them naked.

485
00:40:25,124 --> 00:40:26,707
Yes, sir.

486
00:40:27,416 --> 00:40:29,916
(Donglim)

487
00:40:29,999 --> 00:40:31,415
(Tokyo Op Agents)

488
00:40:31,499 --> 00:40:34,082
(Chief of Team 1 Park Pyong-ho)

489
00:40:36,457 --> 00:40:37,415
Yes.

490
00:40:38,166 --> 00:40:39,916
Wait, right now?

491
00:40:41,166 --> 00:40:42,457
Yes, sir.

492
00:40:43,874 --> 00:40:48,207
Chief Kim is investigating
all agents from the Pyo op.

493
00:40:48,624 --> 00:40:51,124
Must be Director Ahn's order.

494
00:40:57,582 --> 00:41:02,082
Why didn't Agent Yang drive off with
Pyo after making contact?

495
00:41:03,666 --> 00:41:08,166
Our West German bureau fell for
a North Korean plot last year.

496
00:41:08,624 --> 00:41:10,040
Many men got fired,

497
00:41:10,124 --> 00:41:13,332
so now we verify ID and intel on site.

498
00:41:14,374 --> 00:41:17,332
Donglim popped up on our radar
since mid '70s,

499
00:41:17,499 --> 00:41:18,999
but he never fully surfaced.

500
00:41:19,082 --> 00:41:22,040
Donglim may not even exist!

501
00:41:22,291 --> 00:41:26,791
Maybe they want to throw us off by
planting the idea of a mole!

502
00:41:29,416 --> 00:41:33,374
Agent Yang drew up
and led all ops in Japan.

503
00:41:33,541 --> 00:41:35,249
He's the head of Japanese...

504
00:41:35,374 --> 00:41:37,665
Okay, dammit! I'm Donglim!

505
00:41:37,707 --> 00:41:41,748
Chief Kim is Donglim,
you're Donglim! We're all him!

506
00:41:43,249 --> 00:41:47,457
You made anyone into spies,
now you suspect your own?

507
00:41:47,624 --> 00:41:50,749
Check your own unit first, assholes!

508
00:41:51,082 --> 00:41:52,582
That fucking bastard.

509
00:41:52,666 --> 00:41:55,957
What? What can you do? What do you have on me?!

510
00:41:58,374 --> 00:42:02,124
Agent Yang probably got intel
about Donglim from Pyo.

511
00:42:02,249 --> 00:42:06,707
He kept trying to call the former Director
before passing out.

512
00:42:06,916 --> 00:42:10,416
What if Yang intentionally sabotaged the op,

513
00:42:10,499 --> 00:42:12,749
and his intel isn't credible?

514
00:42:12,832 --> 00:42:15,790
Are you implying Agent Yang is Donglim?

515
00:42:17,249 --> 00:42:18,957
That's insane.

516
00:42:19,291 --> 00:42:20,791
What the hell is going on?!

517
00:42:20,874 --> 00:42:24,749
Who authorized this? You have no jurisdiction!

518
00:42:26,416 --> 00:42:28,874
It's an order from the director.

519
00:42:29,124 --> 00:42:32,332
Donglim was part of the Pyo op?

520
00:42:32,541 --> 00:42:35,332
I've worked with all these men
for at least 5 years!

521
00:42:35,541 --> 00:42:38,166
We got a complaint from
Japanese Foreign Affairs.

522
00:42:38,249 --> 00:42:42,165
They want us to investigate
and make an official apology.

523
00:42:42,499 --> 00:42:46,999
If you don't comply,
I'll put you on top of the suspect list.

524
00:42:50,832 --> 00:42:53,457
I'll report to the director myself.

525
00:42:53,541 --> 00:42:55,166
Stop this witch hunt.

526
00:42:55,249 --> 00:42:56,790
Guys, come on out!

527
00:42:56,874 --> 00:42:57,665
Chief!

528
00:42:57,749 --> 00:42:59,207
Don't you dare!

529
00:43:03,832 --> 00:43:04,915
We got an emergency!

530
00:43:04,999 --> 00:43:08,332
A North Korean fighter jet has
entered the South Korean airspace!

531
00:43:21,416 --> 00:43:23,416
This is the Office of Civil Defense,
attention please.

