01:08:40,291 --> 01:08:41,916
Hold them off!

797
01:09:11,582 --> 01:09:13,582
Roof of opposite building, 10 o'clock!

798
01:09:13,791 --> 01:09:15,832
Get to the building!

799
01:09:33,541 --> 01:09:38,041
Li Yong-su is head of the Strategic Unit
at North Korea's Labor Party 35.

800
01:09:39,207 --> 01:09:41,082
He visited Osaka on October 15, 1982,

801
01:09:41,166 --> 01:09:44,374
and Tokyo on May 11, 1983.

802
01:09:44,457 --> 01:09:47,915
We are cross checking all KCIA agent flight logs.

803
01:09:48,249 --> 01:09:52,749
Retired General Kim was pushed out for
not supporting the president's coup,

804
01:09:54,124 --> 01:09:57,749
but Jupiter funds were funneled to him.

805
01:09:57,874 --> 01:10:00,540
He's under house arrest,
so I checked the visitor log,

806
01:10:00,624 --> 01:10:04,957
and found Kim Jung-do in it.

807
01:10:09,666 --> 01:10:11,874
A KCIA agent was assassinated.

808
01:10:11,957 --> 01:10:13,665
While under our protection.

809
01:10:13,749 --> 01:10:15,457
What the hell is going on here?

810
01:10:15,499 --> 01:10:19,999
We've captured a female spy who
relayed Donglim's intel to the North.

811
01:10:21,082 --> 01:10:23,707
We'll expose Donglim soon enough.

812
01:10:23,749 --> 01:10:27,332
We're tracking the finances of a
potential spy organization.

813
01:10:27,832 --> 01:10:30,082
We'll reveal our findings soon.

814
01:10:30,207 --> 01:10:32,207
You mean Jupiter Corp?

815
01:10:33,416 --> 01:10:34,999
Chief Kim.

816
01:10:35,874 --> 01:10:38,999
Didn't you serve with
Jupiter's CEO Choi in the military?

817
01:10:40,874 --> 01:10:45,374
He's just a military supplier now.
I have no ties to him.

818
01:10:55,207 --> 01:10:57,082
Listen you two,

819
01:10:57,332 --> 01:11:01,832
if you want to survive,
wrap it up before the president's Asia tour.

820
01:11:04,374 --> 01:11:07,457
You know what'll happen if you don't.

821
01:11:10,624 --> 01:11:13,415
We've obtained North Korean
Li Yong-su's flight logs to Japan.

822
01:11:13,457 --> 01:11:16,665
Analysts are using 20 IBMs to cross check,
so we'll know soon.

823
01:11:16,832 --> 01:11:19,415
Yes, we'll know your role, too.

824
01:11:19,499 --> 01:11:22,082
Jupiter's CEO Choi will spill everything.

825
01:11:22,166 --> 01:11:24,582
How long do you think that
spy bitch will hold out?

826
01:11:24,666 --> 01:11:26,499
The interrogator can't wait to meet her.

827
01:11:26,582 --> 01:11:29,540
Why'd you transfer Yang out of his room?

828
01:11:29,999 --> 01:11:33,624
The interrogator assured me
he'll get to the bottom of this.

829
01:11:33,707 --> 01:11:36,123
Why move Yang and leave him exposed?!

830
01:11:36,207 --> 01:11:38,165
Don't you dare put his death on me,

831
01:11:38,207 --> 01:11:42,332
just tell me how long you were
in league with that bitch!

832
01:12:03,541 --> 01:12:06,582
That girl's father was my informant in Japan!

833
01:12:06,832 --> 01:12:09,373
He died during my op and
I've been watching over her!

834
01:12:09,499 --> 01:12:13,999
I don't trust your informant,
his bastard child, or even you.

835
01:12:16,749 --> 01:12:19,540
I'm certain you're Donglim.

836
01:12:56,082 --> 01:13:00,582
3 years ago, military coup d'etat and
10-day citizen massacre

837
01:13:49,666 --> 01:13:51,707
Hello, Mr. Kim.

838
01:13:55,707 --> 01:13:57,457
Good to see you..

839
01:14:07,166 --> 01:14:09,082
You stay in Seoul nowadays?

840
01:14:09,166 --> 01:14:11,832
Mostly Hong Kong and Saipan.

841
01:14:11,916 --> 01:14:13,916
How are you doing?

842
01:14:15,082 --> 01:14:19,582
I'm just a white-collar now.
Why did you want to see me?

843
01:14:20,374 --> 01:14:24,165
I have a proposal for you.

844
01:14:24,374 --> 01:14:28,332
Really? If there's any way
I can help, I certainly will.

845
01:14:28,707 --> 01:14:31,207
Not a favor, but a proposal.

846
01:14:34,457 --> 01:14:36,165
What do you have in mind?

847
01:14:36,291 --> 01:14:39,291
The thing you're about to do,

848
01:14:40,624 --> 01:14:42,790
we want you to drop it.

849
01:14:44,207 --> 01:14:46,248
I don't understand you.

850
01:14:46,499 --> 01:14:50,999
I hear Chief Park detained Jupiter's CEO Choi.

851
01:14:56,791 --> 01:14:59,291
Leave for the States.

852
01:15:00,707 --> 01:15:05,207
So long as we're aware of it,
you will not succeed.

853
01:15:07,499 --> 01:15:10,040
I don't understand what you're...

854
01:15:10,166 --> 01:15:12,332
Operation Hunt Peter.

855
01:15:25,707 --> 01:15:28,082
I didn't want to report this at the office

856
01:15:28,166 --> 01:15:31,791
This is a conversation between
General Kim and Chief Kim

857
01:15:31,874 --> 01:15:34,749
before he started working at the agency.

858
01:15:34,832 --> 01:15:39,040
It may not sound like much, but listen carefully.

859
01:15:39,832 --> 01:15:42,207
Your house arrest will end shortly,

860
01:15:42,291 --> 01:15:45,332
and you may have to relocate your cottage.

861
01:15:45,416 --> 01:15:47,166
Is that so?

862
01:15:47,249 --> 01:15:49,874
What's wrong? Don't like the location?

863
01:15:49,957 --> 01:15:51,873
The landlord suddenly changed his mind,

864
01:15:51,957 --> 01:15:55,207
I thought it'd be best to move.

865
01:15:55,291 --> 01:15:58,249
Then it'll have to be redesigned?

866
01:15:58,374 --> 01:16:01,790
In a different location,
the design will have to change.

867
01:16:01,874 --> 01:16:05,540
It isn't easy building a small home.

868
01:16:06,457 --> 01:16:07,623
Do I ask too much?

869
01:16:07,707 --> 01:16:08,873
No, sir.

870
01:16:08,957 --> 01:16:11,582
Just a few minor adjustments.

871
01:16:11,666 --> 01:16:14,499
Once you complete house arrest,
the cottage will be done.

872
01:16:15,332 --> 01:16:17,373
It's tough to hear it over the music, right?

873
01:16:17,457 --> 01:16:20,665
You can still hear their conversation faintly.

874
01:16:20,749 --> 01:16:24,915
So, I got the audio techs to isolate it.

875
01:16:25,041 --> 01:16:26,416
This is it.

876
01:16:29,707 --> 01:16:33,040
It's important to secure funds for extra expenses.

877
01:16:33,166 --> 01:16:37,249
I told Jupiter's Choi to come up with $500,000.

878
01:16:37,374 --> 01:16:41,582
He asked for a week,
I'm sure he'll put it together.

879
01:16:41,707 --> 01:16:45,665
The cottage and the design
refer to their operation.

880
01:16:45,749 --> 01:16:50,124
I'm assigned to KCIA starting next week.

881
01:16:54,999 --> 01:16:58,582
Please be careful.

882
01:16:59,707 --> 01:17:04,207
I'll succeed with Op Hunt Peter
in Washington no matter what.

883
01:17:05,707 --> 01:17:07,207
Peter?

884
01:17:07,666 --> 01:17:10,582
I had so much trouble figuring this part out.

885
01:17:10,749 --> 01:17:12,540
Peter is...

886
01:17:13,249 --> 01:17:15,832
the president's Christian name.

887
01:17:16,332 --> 01:17:18,790
He tried to assassinate the president?

888
01:17:18,916 --> 01:17:22,124
We can't ignore a potential link to the North.

889
01:17:22,207 --> 01:17:25,665
But something's been bothering me.

890
01:17:27,707 --> 01:17:31,165
This is the full list of KCIA agents
who flew to Japan.

891
01:17:31,249 --> 01:17:33,915
Not a single agent was present at the time

892
01:17:33,999 --> 01:17:37,165
Donglim made contact with
North Korea's Li Yong-su.

893
01:17:37,332 --> 01:17:40,540
Chief Kim wasn't present on either date.

894
01:17:40,707 --> 01:17:43,748
You were in Tokyo on May 11, 1983,

895
01:17:43,832 --> 01:17:46,540
but not in Osaka on October 15, 1982.

896
01:17:46,624 --> 01:17:50,457
So, I looked into anyone with a single date match.

897
01:17:50,541 --> 01:17:54,082
Also, about Cho Yoo-jung...

898
01:17:55,624 --> 01:17:57,249
You don't need to worry.

899
01:17:57,332 --> 01:18:00,332
I've asked the JCIA

900
01:18:00,374 --> 01:18:04,499
to confirm her relation to Cho Won-sik,
it'll arrive tomorrow.

901
01:18:05,249 --> 01:18:07,457
Let's see, let's see...

902
01:18:08,957 --> 01:18:13,415
Fly in date is right...

903
01:18:14,666 --> 01:18:16,832
October, October...

904
01:18:20,041 --> 01:18:22,874
Cha Hyung-dae, Osaka, October 15.

905
01:18:23,041 --> 01:18:27,541
He has a fly in date, but no fly out date.

906
01:18:29,832 --> 01:18:32,290
Which means he's a ghost.

907
01:18:34,124 --> 01:18:35,749
Wait a minute.

908
01:18:38,582 --> 01:18:39,373
Cha Hyung-dae.

909
01:18:39,374 --> 01:18:40,665
(Real Name: Park Pyong-ho)
(Aliases: Cha Hyung-dae)

910
01:18:41,999 --> 01:18:46,499
I made you this passport for
last year's West Berlin op...

911
01:18:52,957 --> 01:18:56,457
Sir, you went to Japan with this passport?

912
01:19:09,416 --> 01:19:11,124
Ju-kyung...

913
01:19:15,999 --> 01:19:17,957
You're the one?

914
01:19:18,624 --> 01:19:20,290
Wait a minute!

915
01:19:23,207 --> 01:19:24,748
Wait, don't come any closer.

916
01:19:24,832 --> 01:19:25,915
Ju-kyung.

917
01:19:26,957 --> 01:19:28,790
Stop right there!

918
01:20:52,207 --> 01:20:55,498
My government has accepted this administration.

919
01:20:55,832 --> 01:20:58,207
What we want is simple.

920
01:20:58,624 --> 01:21:00,207
We want order.

921
01:21:02,082 --> 01:21:04,248
Forget everything, and leave.

922
01:21:04,332 --> 01:21:08,207
We'll support you and your family.

923
01:21:11,166 --> 01:21:14,541
The military assault that started on May 18th

924
01:21:14,957 --> 01:21:19,457
resulted in over 3,000 civilian
casualties in 10 days.

925
01:21:21,707 --> 01:21:26,207
On the 21st,
there was even an attack by helicopters.

926
01:21:29,749 --> 01:21:32,457
Youngest casualty was a 11-year-old child.

927
01:21:34,374 --> 01:21:38,874
A bullet passed through his chest,
and killed him instantly.

928
01:21:45,124 --> 01:21:48,874
You want me to accept the killer of my people,

929
01:21:49,999 --> 01:21:52,624
and turn my back on my country?

930
01:21:54,499 --> 01:21:57,124
Your proposal is very insulting.

931
01:22:17,749 --> 01:22:18,749
Hello?

932
01:22:18,832 --> 01:22:22,290
Sir, it's me! Chief Park is Donglim!

933
01:22:22,582 --> 01:22:25,748
He killed Agent Bang Ju-kyung and is on the move!

934
01:22:25,832 --> 01:22:27,957
- What's his current location?
- Heading towards Mapo!

935
01:22:28,041 --> 01:22:30,082
I'm on my way, have our men ready!

936
01:22:30,166 --> 01:22:31,499
Yes, sir!

937
01:22:46,416 --> 01:22:47,416
(Hunt South Korea's #1 in Bangkok on the 11th,
intel by Donglim)

938
01:22:47,416 --> 01:22:49,499
The president's revised itinerary.

939
01:22:49,582 --> 01:22:52,248
I need to meet the head
of the South Korean cell.

940
01:22:52,332 --> 01:22:54,540
You know cells can't meet face-to-face.

941
01:22:54,624 --> 01:22:57,290
Think we're in Storm Level 1?

942
01:22:58,374 --> 01:23:01,165
Who cares about that, just make contact!

943
01:23:02,624 --> 01:23:05,540
I'll hand this off in person.

944
01:23:17,791 --> 01:23:19,291
People are coming out.

945
01:23:19,374 --> 01:23:21,040
People are exiting the church.

946
01:23:21,124 --> 01:23:21,874
And Park Pyung-ho?

947
01:23:21,957 --> 01:23:23,248
Not yet, sir.

948
01:23:23,332 --> 01:23:24,540
Dammit.

949
01:23:25,332 --> 01:23:29,290
Follow every one of them! Don't miss a single one!

950
01:23:29,749 --> 01:23:31,540
Follow your mark.

951
01:24:12,749 --> 01:24:14,249
Agent Jang.

952
01:24:14,707 --> 01:24:16,457
Why are you here?

953
01:24:17,332 --> 01:24:19,957
Chief Park, I'm...

954
01:24:20,874 --> 01:24:24,499
You're what? Are you tailing me?

955
01:24:24,707 --> 01:24:27,373
No, it's not that.

956
01:24:29,166 --> 01:24:30,749
Chief!

957
01:24:46,416 --> 01:24:50,916
Jeez, KCIA fuckers sure suck at their job.

958
01:24:54,874 --> 01:24:59,207
How could they go easy on a commie like this one?

959
01:25:00,124 --> 01:25:03,082
Which agency do you work for?

960
01:25:03,707 --> 01:25:05,915
Don't play dumb.

961
01:25:06,541 --> 01:25:10,416
Defense Security Command,
you can't weasel out this time.

962
01:25:10,832 --> 01:25:12,540
Lift him up!

963
01:25:16,082 --> 01:25:19,873
Call Captain Kwon at once and free me!

964
01:25:20,249 --> 01:25:22,499
You're best buds with my captain?

965
01:25:23,332 --> 01:25:25,873
Go on, give him a massage.

966
01:25:38,916 --> 01:25:41,874
So? You feel like talking now?

967
01:25:42,624 --> 01:25:44,749
Did Kim Jung-do send you?

968
01:25:44,832 --> 01:25:47,832
You think killing me will save Jupiter Corp?

969
01:25:48,041 --> 01:25:51,457
You think I don't know about
Operation Hunt Peter?!

970
01:25:51,832 --> 01:25:54,707
What's this asshole blabbering on about?

971
01:25:54,791 --> 01:25:59,291
Get a whiff of your burning skin and die!

972
01:26:02,291 --> 01:26:05,457
That college chick of yours spilled her guts!

973
01:26:05,541 --> 01:26:09,124
That you're Donglim,
who's been spying on the KCIA for 13 years!

974
01:26:09,499 --> 01:26:12,874
She's on the way here, so fess up first.

975
01:26:13,291 --> 01:26:16,541
Only one of you will get to live.

976
01:26:16,874 --> 01:26:20,124
Call the KCIA now...

977
01:26:21,082 --> 01:26:22,665
Lieutenant Min! Bring the documents.

978
01:26:22,791 --> 01:26:25,874
This fucker still thinks he's a KCIA agent.

979
01:26:26,749 --> 01:26:28,499
Look at it, it's your handwriting.

980
01:26:28,582 --> 01:26:31,957
"Hunt South Korea's #1" Assassinate our president?

981
01:26:34,041 --> 01:26:38,541
It's a controlled leak, you stupid thug!

982
01:26:41,707 --> 01:26:43,498
Bring him out.

983
01:26:48,291 --> 01:26:49,791
Fucking commies.

984
01:26:55,249 --> 01:26:56,749
State your objective!

985
01:26:56,832 --> 01:26:57,915
You goddamn traitors!

986
01:26:57,999 --> 01:27:00,165
You'll be punished for high treason...

987
01:27:08,499 --> 01:27:10,124
Who are you?

988
01:27:11,249 --> 01:27:13,374
State your objective!

989
01:27:15,707 --> 01:27:17,623
Who are you?!

990
01:27:30,749 --> 01:27:32,749
You did well, comrade Donglim.

991
01:27:32,832 --> 01:27:35,123
Been a while since your last loyalty check.

992
01:27:35,207 --> 01:27:39,207
I'm chief of the Ministry of
People's Armed Forces.

993
01:27:40,207 --> 01:27:43,582
Why's the MPAF involved in this operation?

994
01:27:44,249 --> 01:27:48,582
Connect me to the United Front's Li Yong-su.

995
01:27:50,707 --> 01:27:55,207
You won't hear that peace lover's cries for
negotiation ever again.

996
01:27:59,791 --> 01:28:01,332
Our leader changed the plan.

997
01:28:01,416 --> 01:28:05,291
Starting with Operation Flare,
we'll attack the South militarily.

998
01:28:06,666 --> 01:28:08,499
Operation Flare?

999
01:28:08,582 --> 01:28:10,415
That's nonsense, an all-out-war?!

1000
01:28:11,499 --> 01:28:14,040
You think the US will just stand by?

1001
01:28:14,124 --> 01:28:18,624
Doesn't matter, 6 hours is
all we need to take the South.

1002
01:28:19,332 --> 01:28:23,457
But millions will die in those 6 hours!

1003
01:28:24,749 --> 01:28:27,415
Our original plan to negotiate

1004
01:28:27,499 --> 01:28:30,457
after killing their president is most practical!

1005
01:28:32,082 --> 01:28:34,832
Reunification is the party's goal, no?!

1006
01:28:34,916 --> 01:28:38,041
Do not spoil the plan for peaceful revolution

1007
01:28:38,124 --> 01:28:39,082
Comrade.

1008
01:28:39,166 --> 01:28:41,999
Peaceful reunification is an illusion.

1009
01:28:42,082 --> 01:28:44,915
Your mission from now is to
assist in the assassination.

1010
01:28:44,916 --> 01:28:45,749
(Hunt #1, then kill Donglim)

1011
01:28:45,749 --> 01:28:48,790
By accompanying the president on his Asian tour.

1012
01:28:50,916 --> 01:28:52,832
I cannot agree to that!

1013
01:28:53,041 --> 01:28:56,832
You think I stayed alive this long
just to start a war?!

1014
01:28:58,207 --> 01:29:01,498
Having some intel makes you better than us?!

1015
01:29:01,624 --> 01:29:02,624
How dare you disobey an order!

1016
01:29:02,707 --> 01:29:04,748
I can't agree to a war!

1017
01:29:10,582 --> 01:29:14,457
This will destroy all of us...

1018
01:29:39,332 --> 01:29:40,748
Get the rifles!

1019
01:30:15,124 --> 01:30:18,124
(Hunt #1, then kill Donglim)

1020
01:30:23,249 --> 01:30:24,957
Back door! Back door!

1021
01:30:25,041 --> 01:30:26,124
Go after him!

1022
01:30:26,207 --> 01:30:28,040
You two, go upstairs!

1023
01:30:38,749 --> 01:30:40,749
(Peaceful revolution.)

1024
01:30:40,832 --> 01:30:43,373
(Hunt South Korea #1
after verse 1 of National Anthem.)

1025
01:30:43,457 --> 01:30:45,623
(Intel gathered by Donglim)

1026
01:30:48,707 --> 01:30:50,207
(Peaceful Revolution #1)

1027
01:30:56,291 --> 01:30:57,791
(Park Pyong-ho)

1028
01:31:05,707 --> 01:31:07,123
(Hunt #1, then kill Donglim)

1029
01:31:21,791 --> 01:31:23,332
Free Chief Park!

1030
01:31:54,374 --> 01:31:56,415
Donglim has been killed.

1031
01:32:10,124 --> 01:32:11,749
CEO Choi...

1032
01:32:13,457 --> 01:32:15,415
Where is he now?

1033
01:32:19,832 --> 01:32:24,040
The director wants CEO Choi's confession today,
whatever it takes.

1034
01:32:27,332 --> 01:32:28,707
Who are you?!

1035
01:32:41,457 --> 01:32:43,082
CEO Choi.

1036
01:32:52,457 --> 01:32:55,582
What exactly is Jupiter Corp?

1037
01:32:58,416 --> 01:33:02,416
Who are you in league with?

1038
01:33:08,499 --> 01:33:10,249
All right, fine.

1039
01:33:11,874 --> 01:33:14,624
You really want to go all the way?

1040
01:33:22,291 --> 01:33:23,749
Spill it.

1041
01:33:24,624 --> 01:33:27,832
Who's involved and what's their end goal.

1042
01:33:28,957 --> 01:33:31,873
If you don't tell us, you die.

1043
01:33:33,124 --> 01:33:34,624
Very well.

1044
01:33:37,249 --> 01:33:39,290
That's what I wanted.

1045
01:33:45,457 --> 01:33:46,832
Give me your best shot.

1046
01:33:59,791 --> 01:34:03,041
Sir, if we go any higher he could die.

1047
01:34:57,124 --> 01:34:58,915
Status on CEO Choi?

1048
01:35:00,624 --> 01:35:05,124
He was a soldier to the end.

1049
01:35:08,999 --> 01:35:12,165
But the hunt of Peter is possible.

1050
01:35:12,541 --> 01:35:15,124
North Korea has a plan in motion

1051
01:35:16,499 --> 01:35:19,540
to assassinate the president on
October 11th at 10 AM in Bangkok.

1052
01:35:19,624 --> 01:35:22,124
What? North Koreans?

1053
01:35:23,166 --> 01:35:27,374
We obtained this intel at a raid
we conducted today.

1054
01:35:29,416 --> 01:35:31,957
Once they successfully assassinate the president,

1055
01:35:32,082 --> 01:35:36,290
we can initiate Operation New World.

1056
01:35:36,416 --> 01:35:40,082
You want to carry out a joint op with the North?

1057
01:35:40,166 --> 01:35:40,957
That's preposterous.

1058
01:35:41,041 --> 01:35:44,416
How is that a revolution?
It has to be justified.

1059
01:35:44,499 --> 01:35:45,957
We'll hold hands with commies?

1060
01:35:46,041 --> 01:35:48,291
This is not a revolution!

1061
01:35:52,166 --> 01:35:56,666
It's about stopping the
violence against our people.

1062
01:36:01,457 --> 01:36:03,832
That's our justification.

1063
01:36:08,249 --> 01:36:11,749
I'm flying out to Bangkok tomorrow.

1064
01:36:22,124 --> 01:36:24,957
Go as far South as possible.

1065
01:36:25,957 --> 01:36:29,790
Take the first bus to Namhae.

1066
01:36:30,999 --> 01:36:35,332
In Namhae, there's a temple called Boriam.

1067
01:36:36,499 --> 01:36:38,249
Go there.

1068
01:36:39,082 --> 01:36:41,082
It should be safe there.

1069
01:36:42,499 --> 01:36:43,999
What's going on?

1070
01:36:45,999 --> 01:36:49,915
No matter what happens in South Korea,
stay at the temple.

1071
01:36:51,541 --> 01:36:53,832
What's happening?

1072
01:38:37,957 --> 01:38:42,415
Bangkok

1073
01:38:48,707 --> 01:38:52,123
Reunification is at the tip of our barrels.

1074
01:38:53,082 --> 01:38:56,582
We'll celebrate our Grand Marshal
upon reunification.

1075
01:38:58,541 --> 01:39:02,124
The party has initiated Operation Flare.

1076
01:39:03,291 --> 01:39:07,624
It'll ignite on verse 1,
last line of the South Korean anthem.

1077
01:39:08,916 --> 01:39:11,457
For our party and our country!

1078
01:39:12,166 --> 01:39:14,082
To our Grand Marshal!

1079
01:39:14,249 --> 01:39:16,707
To our Grand Marshal! To our Grand Marshal!

1080
01:40:10,666 --> 01:40:12,957
Main gate, sitrep.

1081
01:40:13,291 --> 01:40:14,791
All in order, sir.

1082
01:40:14,957 --> 01:40:17,707
Report when you see the motorcade approaching.

1083
01:40:17,832 --> 01:40:19,123
Yes, sir!

1084
01:40:21,791 --> 01:40:24,291
Why did you let me walk?

1085
01:40:25,332 --> 01:40:27,582
You know who I am.

1086
01:40:27,666 --> 01:40:30,707
You know what I'm trying to do.

1087
01:40:34,791 --> 01:40:37,666
How long can you fight violence with violence?

1088
01:40:39,707 --> 01:40:43,207
You think the world will change by
removing one dictator?

1089
01:40:45,374 --> 01:40:48,832
You've seen how this dictatorship evolved.

1090
01:40:49,332 --> 01:40:51,290
It's time to end it.

1091
01:40:56,124 --> 01:40:59,165
Once the president arrives,
when does the anthem begin?

1092
01:40:59,457 --> 01:41:00,707
Yes, sir.

1093
01:41:00,791 --> 01:41:03,499
It'll start once they pass the memorial.

1094
01:41:03,957 --> 01:41:07,457
Once he's assassinated, the invasion begins.

1095
01:41:08,124 --> 01:41:10,249
That's North Korea's plan.

1096
01:41:12,749 --> 01:41:14,957
Reunification by force?

1097
01:41:15,874 --> 01:41:19,290
Are you still fooled by such political theater?

1098
01:41:23,791 --> 01:41:26,582
What do you want from me?

1099
01:41:27,791 --> 01:41:31,041
Our goals are the same,
we can join up temporarily.

1100
01:41:33,041 --> 01:41:34,707
And then?

1101
01:41:37,666 --> 01:41:39,707
After that?

1102
01:41:41,874 --> 01:41:42,874
This is the main gate.

1103
01:41:42,957 --> 01:41:46,082
The director, ministers,
and reporters are heading in.

1104
01:41:47,249 --> 01:41:48,707
Roger.

1105
01:41:49,582 --> 01:41:51,498
No mistakes.

1106
01:42:14,957 --> 01:42:17,332
Good work, gents.

1107
01:42:17,457 --> 01:42:19,498
Let's all have a drink after this is over.

1108
01:42:19,582 --> 01:42:21,373
Let's go inside.

1109
01:42:33,166 --> 01:42:35,416
Main gate, sitrep!
Has the president arrived?

1110
01:42:35,499 --> 01:42:37,040
Main gate!

1111
01:42:41,541 --> 01:42:43,582
Go confirm!

1112
01:42:53,457 --> 01:42:56,373
It's not the president!
It's Korean Ambassador to Thailand!

1113
01:42:56,707 --> 01:42:58,457
Stop the anthem!

1114
01:42:59,416 --> 01:43:00,874
Stop the anthem!

1115
01:43:00,957 --> 01:43:02,748
Stop! Stop it!

1116
01:43:03,166 --> 01:43:04,249
Stop!

1117
01:43:21,041 --> 01:43:23,291
The escort made you look like the president.

1118
01:43:23,374 --> 01:43:24,540
He will be arriving shortly.

1119
01:43:24,624 --> 01:43:26,207
- I see.
- Let's go inside.

1120
01:43:46,207 --> 01:43:48,582
I'll send you wherever you want to go.

1121
01:43:49,041 --> 01:43:51,749
When it's all over.

1122
01:44:08,832 --> 01:44:11,498
Chief Kim, come say hello.

1123
01:44:14,749 --> 01:44:16,832
You've done a marvelous job.

1124
01:44:19,374 --> 01:44:21,415
Reunification at last.

1125
01:44:21,916 --> 01:44:25,249
He'll be a great support back home in the future.

1126
01:44:25,666 --> 01:44:30,166
Comrade, with Operation Flare,
South Korea will be destroyed.

1127
01:44:40,457 --> 01:44:43,707
This is the main gate,
the president is passing through.

1128
01:44:47,332 --> 01:44:50,290
The party and our country are watching you today.

1129
01:44:55,916 --> 01:44:57,541
Good luck to you.

1130
01:45:15,166 --> 01:45:17,082
North Korean spy...

1131
01:45:19,291 --> 01:45:21,124
It's a sniper!

1132
01:45:42,666 --> 01:45:44,499
Stop the anthem!

1133
01:45:44,916 --> 01:45:46,332
Stop the anthem!

1134
01:45:48,499 --> 01:45:50,332
What's going on?!

1135
01:45:51,291 --> 01:45:53,416
Stop!

1136
01:45:53,791 --> 01:45:55,582
Stop!

1137
01:46:02,582 --> 01:46:04,373
Sniper!

1138
01:47:07,957 --> 01:47:10,332
Chief Kim, go rescue the president!

1139
01:47:11,374 --> 01:47:14,040
What are you doing?! Go rescue him!

1140
01:47:14,124 --> 01:47:16,249
Why should I rescue him?!

1141
01:47:57,374 --> 01:47:59,374
Stop it! No!

1142
01:48:01,541 --> 01:48:02,916
Stop!

1143
01:49:40,374 --> 01:49:43,040
Lower your gun. Don't do this.

1144
01:49:46,207 --> 01:49:49,248
Stop! Everyone stop!

1145
01:49:51,124 --> 01:49:55,624
You're sentenced to death for usurping power
and murdering our people.

1146
01:49:55,791 --> 01:49:57,499
Chief Kim!

1147
01:49:59,166 --> 01:50:00,541
Chief Kim!

1148
01:51:14,832 --> 01:51:17,082
Bring the car over!

1149
01:51:18,457 --> 01:51:22,082
Bring the car! Get the car over here!

1150
01:51:29,166 --> 01:51:31,832
Mr. President! Are you okay?!

1151
01:51:47,582 --> 01:51:49,165
Drive!

1152
01:52:37,041 --> 01:52:38,666
Park Pyong-ho!

1153
01:52:41,207 --> 01:52:43,373
Park Pyong-ho!

1154
01:52:46,416 --> 01:52:48,332
Park Pyong-ho!

1155
01:52:53,166 --> 01:52:54,916
Park Pyong-ho!

1156
01:52:57,791 --> 01:52:59,582
Park Pyong-ho!

1157
01:53:24,999 --> 01:53:26,665
Why?

1158
01:53:28,416 --> 01:53:30,749
Why did you do it?!

1159
01:53:30,874 --> 01:53:32,082
Hold still,

1160
01:53:32,166 --> 01:53:33,666
you can survive this.

1161
01:53:41,874 --> 01:53:44,082
Did you want to live?

1162
01:55:18,832 --> 01:55:20,540
One moment.

1163
01:55:24,499 --> 01:55:27,457
Release her. And give this to her.

1164
01:55:35,874 --> 01:55:37,457
Uncuff her.

1165
01:55:58,249 --> 01:56:01,999
Pull out.

1166
01:56:26,874 --> 01:56:31,374
My mission was to watch you.

1167
01:56:31,874 --> 01:56:35,290
Soon, someone else will come.

1168
01:59:04,166 --> 01:59:05,957
Yoo-jung...

1169
01:59:10,041 --> 01:59:13,332
you can live a different life.

1170
01:59:31,499 --> 01:59:34,665
(Park Eun-su)

